# M5 P07 — End-to-end CTF flow on a map authored in the level editor.
#
# Pairs with tools/editor/shots/ctf_map.shot (which wrote the .lvl).
# Verifies:
#   1. The .lvl loads, flags are populated by ctf_init_round.
#   2. Touch-driven pickup fires when the player walks into the
#      enemy (BLUE) flag.
#   3. Walking the picked-up flag back to the home (RED) flag
#      triggers the both-flags-home capture rule.
#   4. The capture awards score (R 5 - B 0 since CTF score limit
#      clamps to 5).
#
# Map layout (from ctf_map.shot — 50×16 tiles = 1600×512 px):
#   Red flag  at (200, 332), Red spawn  at (150, 348)
#   Blue flag at (1400, 332), Blue spawn at (1450, 348)
#
# We `spawn_at` the player just east of the BLUE flag so the test
# completes in ~5 seconds: walk LEFT into Blue flag (pickup), keep
# walking LEFT all the way back to Red flag (capture).

window 1280 720
out build/shots/m5_ctf_editor_map
seed 1 2

load_lvl assets/maps/ctf_test.lvl
mode ctf

# Park the player just east of the BLUE flag (x=1400). The dummy
# (team 2, BLUE) spawns at the level's authored spawn (1450, 348)
# and stays put. Walking LEFT brings us within touch radius (36 px).
spawn_at 1480 332

contact_sheet sheet cols 4 cell 320 180

at 1   shot t1_round_start
at 30  shot t30_settled

# Walk LEFT to grab the BLUE flag. ~80 px traversal at 4.66 px/tick
# means pickup fires around tick 50. Continue holding LEFT all the
# way back across the map to the RED flag at x=200; ~1280 px takes
# ~275 ticks.
at 35  press left
at 60  shot t60_after_pickup

# Keep holding LEFT until the player reaches the RED home flag.
at 350 release left

at 200 shot t200_running_home
at 320 shot t320_capturing
at 360 shot t360_post_capture

at 420 end
